#MEM id=panning-for-gold source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/kai/skills/marketplace/panning-for-gold/SKILL.md
M|panning-for-gold|name: panning-for-gold
M|panning-for-gold|version: 1.0.0
M|panning-for-gold|model: claude-sonnet-4-6
M|panning-for-gold|description: "Triage raw unstructured input (transcripts, brain dumps) into evaluated thread inventories and a synthesized gold-found file across three phases."
M|panning-for-gold|license: MIT
M|panning-for-gold|Turn raw, unstructured capture into an evaluated, actionable inventory of threads. Three phases: Extract, Evaluate, Synthesize.
M|panning-for-gold|| Trigger Phrase | Operation |
M|panning-for-gold||----------------|-----------|
M|panning-for-gold|| `pan for gold` | Run the full extract -> evaluate -> synthesize procedure |
M|panning-for-gold|| `triage transcript` | Build inventory of threads from a raw transcript |
M|panning-for-gold|| `synthesize gold-found` | gen the final gold-found file from evaluations |
M|panning-for-gold|Use this skill when:
M|panning-for-gold|- You have a voice transcript, stream-of-consciousness note, or brain dump that contains many ideas mixed with noise.
M|panning-for-gold|- You need a deterministic procedure to triage which ideas merit deeper analysis.
M|panning-for-gold|- You want a permanent, structured artifact that downstream agents (analyst, spec-generator) can consume.
M|panning-for-gold|Use a different skill when:
M|panning-for-gold|- The input is already structured (specs, ADRs, code). Use the analyst or spec-generator agents instead.
M|panning-for-gold|- You only need a one-off summary. Use a generic summarizer.
M|panning-for-gold|The skill operates inside a workspace root. The default is `./.panning/` in the current working directory; override via `--workspace <path>` or the `PANNING_WORKSPACE` environment variable.
M|panning-for-gold|```text
M|panning-for-gold|<workspace>/
M|panning-for-gold||-- transcripts/          # Raw input (read-only after capture)
M|panning-for-gold||-- inventories/          # Pass1 + final inventories
M|panning-for-gold||-- evaluations/          # Per-thread evaluation files
M|panning-for-gold|`-- gold-found/           # Synthesized gold-found files
M|panning-for-gold|```
M|panning-for-gold|The script creates missing subdirectories on demand. It never overwrites an existing file unless `--force` is passed.
M|panning-for-gold|Build a pass1 inventory from a transcript without filtering. Every thread that surfaces is recorded.
M|panning-for-gold|Each thread block uses this structure:
M|panning-for-gold|```markdown
M|panning-for-gold|- **Signal**: high | medium | low
M|panning-for-gold|- **Quote**: "<verbatim quote that surfaced this thread>"
M|panning-for-gold|- **ctx**: <one sentence on where this came from>
M|panning-for-gold|- **Initial take**: <one sentence on why this might matter>
M|panning-for-gold|```
M|panning-for-gold|The pass1 inventory is provisional. A second pass refines and merges into a final inventory.
M|panning-for-gold|For each thread in the final inventory, write an evaluation file. The evaluation captures depth: what evidence supports the thread, what would falsify it, what action it implies.
M|panning-for-gold|Evaluations are independent. They can be authored serially or in parallel.
M|panning-for-gold|Combine the final inventory and the evaluation files into a gold-found markdown file. The gold-found file groups threads by signal level (High, Medium, Low) and includes a metadata block at the top.
M|panning-for-gold|```text
M|panning-for-gold|pan.py init      --workspace <path>
M|panning-for-gold|pan.py validate  --inventory <file>
M|panning-for-gold|pan.py merge     --pass1 <file> --final <file> --output <file>
M|panning-for-gold|pan.py synth     --inventory <file> --evaluations <dir> --output <file>
M|panning-for-gold|```
M|panning-for-gold|The script delegates to `inventory.py` for parsing and merging, and `synthesis.py` for gold-found generation.
M|panning-for-gold|- [ ] Inventory thread blocks contain `Signal`, `Quote`, `ctx`, `Initial take` fields.
M|panning-for-gold|- [ ] Final inventory deduplicates threads from pass1 by title.
M|panning-for-gold|- [ ] Gold-found file has a metadata block plus High-Signal, Medium-Signal, and Low-Signal sections in that order.
M|panning-for-gold|- [ ] No threads from the inventory are silently dropped.
M|panning-for-gold|- `references/inventory-template.md` - thread inventory skeleton.
M|panning-for-gold|- `references/gold-found-template.md` - gold-found skeleton.